title: Cadillac unveils monument on 40th anniversary of Kiss visit
text: > Entertainment Cadillac unveils monument on 40th anniversary of Kiss visit FILE-- In this Oct. 9, 1975 file photo, members of the rock band KISS, from top left: Paul Stanley, Peter Criss, Ace Frehley and Gene Simmons, line up behind two members of the Cadillac High School Vikings football team, wearing KISS facepaint, in Cadillac, Mich. The small northern Michigan city is celebrating the 40th anniversary of an unforgettable visit by rock 'n' roll band Kiss with two days of events and a monument dedicated to the band. (Mike McCarty/Cadillac News via AP, File)
